// PropertiesPanel
// Right-side properties inspector for the design editor.
// Shows position/size/rotation/opacity/fills/strokes/text/auto-layout controls
// for the selected node(s).

NumericInput, Label, SectionTitle, Divider are small stateless UI primitives.

FUNCTION FillsSection(node) -> JSX
  Renders each fill as a ColorPicker swatch.
  On first color drag, captures original fills for undo grouping.
  handleColorChange: updates fills optimistically (no undo until commit).
  handleColorCommit: commits fill change with original fills for undo.
  addFill: appends a new white fill.

---

FUNCTION StrokesSection(node) -> JSX
  Same pattern as FillsSection but for strokes.

---

FUNCTION TextSection(node) -> JSX
  Inputs for fontSize, fontWeight, textAlignHorizontal (L/C/R/J buttons),
  letterSpacing, lineHeight.

---

FUNCTION AutoLayoutSection(node) -> JSX
  Only rendered when layoutMode !== 'NONE'.
  Toggle for horizontal/vertical layout, itemSpacing, four padding inputs.

---

FUNCTION PropertiesPanel() -> JSX                                      EXPORT
  Reads selectedIds and nodes from designEditorStore.
  IF no selection: shows "Select a node to edit properties" empty state.
  IF ≥2 nodes: shows alignment buttons.
  IF exactly 1 node: shows full property inspector (position, size, rotation,
  cornerRadius, opacity, FillsSection, StrokesSection, TextSection,
  AutoLayoutSection).
